1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,335
Previously on Riverdale...

2
00:00:01,338 --> 00:00:03,642
We will not rest until those responsible

3
00:00:03,645 --> 00:00:06,813
for the murder of our
sister is rightly punished.

4
00:00:06,815 --> 00:00:07,981
Fangs...

5
00:00:07,984 --> 00:00:11,216
Mrs. Klump, the Sheriff's department
is working around the clock...

6
00:00:11,219 --> 00:00:13,945
You were supposed to be
protecting our children.

7
00:00:13,948 --> 00:00:16,015
- What's all this?
- It's ransom money.

8
00:00:16,018 --> 00:00:17,784
Not for Archie, I got him back.

9
00:00:17,787 --> 00:00:19,828
This is from when I
turned the tables on Nick,

10
00:00:19,831 --> 00:00:21,567
and held him for ransom instead.

11
00:00:21,570 --> 00:00:23,411
I still haven't made my bones with you.

12
00:00:23,414 --> 00:00:26,799
There's only one man I'm interested
in bringing down, the Black Hood.

13
00:00:26,801 --> 00:00:30,304
And whatever I can do to help you
on your quest, you can count on me.

14
00:00:30,307 --> 00:00:32,156
This is the Black Hood speaking.

15
00:00:32,159 --> 00:00:35,976
I got a letter. These symbols
look so familiar to me.

16
00:00:35,979 --> 00:00:38,257
I used to check out
this book obsessively.

17
00:00:38,260 --> 00:00:40,113
Betty, how could the
Black Hood know that?

18
00:00:40,115 --> 00:00:41,648
Put it on.

19
00:00:41,651 --> 00:00:43,257
Why are you doing this to me?

20
00:00:43,260 --> 00:00:45,250
To show you that we're the same.

21
00:00:45,253 --> 00:00:48,078
Where is he, Betty?
Where did you take Chic?

22
00:00:48,081 --> 00:00:49,562
Did you kill my brother?

23
00:00:49,565 --> 00:00:51,005
I didn't mean to hurt him.

24
00:00:51,695 --> 00:00:53,560
I'm gonna give you a head start.

25
00:00:57,219 --> 00:00:58,852
Mom, where's dad?

26
00:01:07,175 --> 00:01:08,398
- Hello.
- Hello, Sir.

27
00:01:08,401 --> 00:01:10,281
I'm campaigning for
my dad, Fred Andrews.

28
00:01:10,284 --> 00:01:12,712
He's running for Mayor of Riverdale
and could really use your vote.

29
00:01:12,714 --> 00:01:14,547
On the eve of the Mayoral Debate,

30
00:01:14,549 --> 00:01:16,983
as Archie Andrews goes door-to-door,

31
00:01:18,720 --> 00:01:22,632
he doesn't mention the murder
of his classmate, Midge Klump.

32
00:01:22,635 --> 00:01:23,914
Excuse me, sir.

33
00:01:23,917 --> 00:01:25,925
I'm campaigning for
my dad, Fred Andrews.

34
00:01:25,928 --> 00:01:27,494
I'm voting for Hiram Lodge.

35
00:01:27,497 --> 00:01:29,163
Don't you mean Hermione Lodge?

36
00:01:30,799 --> 00:01:33,062
Take the flyer, sir, in
case you change your mind.

37
00:01:33,065 --> 00:01:34,093
Sure.

38
00:01:34,096 --> 00:01:36,906
Most people believed Midge
was murdered by someone else

39
00:01:38,373 --> 00:01:39,706
but not Archie.

40
00:01:39,708 --> 00:01:42,208
He was certain, beyond
a shadow of a doubt,

41
00:01:42,210 --> 00:01:43,743
the Black Hood was back,

42
00:01:43,746 --> 00:01:46,579
as was his next-door
neighbor, Betty Cooper.

43
00:01:46,581 --> 00:01:49,816
Who had, in fact, laid
eyes on the Black Hood

44
00:01:49,819 --> 00:01:52,505
and suspected he was much closer.

45
00:01:53,455 --> 00:01:55,355
Penny for your thoughts, hon?

46
00:01:57,325 --> 00:02:00,827
I was thinking that he was a test.

47
00:02:02,263 --> 00:02:03,463
Who was?

48
00:02:03,465 --> 00:02:05,365
The impostor, Chic.

49
00:02:05,367 --> 00:02:09,002
Everything that he did
to us and brought to us,

50
00:02:09,004 --> 00:02:11,704
was kind of a test.

51
00:02:11,707 --> 00:02:14,474
But we survived and
we're stronger for it.

52
00:02:14,476 --> 00:02:16,262
Well, that remains to be seen.

53
00:02:16,265 --> 00:02:18,356
No, Mom, we are.

54
00:02:18,359 --> 00:02:21,328
And we'll survive
whatever else comes next.

55
00:02:26,287 --> 00:02:28,087
You can't see my bruises anymore.

56
00:02:28,089 --> 00:02:30,456
Yes, no reason whatsoever to bring up

57
00:02:30,458 --> 00:02:33,326
Nick's failed attempt
to kidnap and murder you.

58
00:02:33,329 --> 00:02:36,997
Speaking of, there is one
thing I wanted to tell you.

59
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:38,128
What's that?

60
00:02:38,131 --> 00:02:41,199
Word of my exploits
serving Nick his comeuppance

61
00:02:41,202 --> 00:02:44,637
has seeped into the demimonde
of mobsters and molls

62
00:02:44,639 --> 00:02:46,806
my father used to associate with,

63
00:02:46,809 --> 00:02:50,361
so the five families are sending
their youngest and brightest

64
00:02:50,364 --> 00:02:52,045
their "princes," as it were

65
00:02:52,047 --> 00:02:55,581
to, well, come court
the rare Mafia Princess

66
00:02:55,583 --> 00:02:57,650
who can belly up to the
bar with the big boys.

67
00:02:57,652 --> 00:02:59,185
What do you mean, "Court"?

68
00:02:59,187 --> 00:03:02,488
Thanks to my play, the families
are looking to make a business

69
00:03:02,490 --> 00:03:05,124
and/or political
alliances with my parents.

70
00:03:05,126 --> 00:03:07,226
It's all very Borgia-Medici.

71
00:03:07,228 --> 00:03:09,729
Archie, if you have a moment?

72
00:03:09,731 --> 00:03:11,531
Go ahead. We'll meet up at lunch,

73
00:03:11,533 --> 00:03:13,866
after I welcome the tributes.

74
00:03:15,570 --> 00:03:18,705
My spies tell me you're out
campaigning for your father.

75
00:03:18,707 --> 00:03:21,274
I'm not campaigning, Mr. Lodge.

76
00:03:21,277 --> 00:03:22,995
I'm trying to find the Black Hood.

77
00:03:22,998 --> 00:03:26,370
It sounds insane, but
I remember his eyes.

78
00:03:26,373 --> 00:03:29,120
So I'm going house-to-house to...

79
00:03:29,123 --> 00:03:31,150
Stare into men's eyes?

80
00:03:31,153 --> 00:03:34,019
Well, that sounds like looking
for a needle in a haystack,

81
00:03:34,022 --> 00:03:36,823
but we don't even know if that
the needle is in the haystack.

82
00:03:36,825 --> 00:03:39,592
You said you wanted to make
your bones. Is that still true?

83
00:03:41,763 --> 00:03:43,730
- Yes.
- Well, then...

84
00:03:45,234 --> 00:03:47,533
Why don't you reform your Dark Circle?

85
00:03:47,535 --> 00:03:50,069
You'll want back-up should
you identify the Black Hood.

86
00:03:50,071 --> 00:03:53,172
Reggie and the guys are
fired-up, Mr. Lodge, for sure,

87
00:03:53,174 --> 00:03:57,143
but I need focused
lasers, not loose cannons.

88
00:03:57,146 --> 00:03:58,312
To help with that...

89
00:03:58,315 --> 00:04:01,261
A new Sheriff's taken over
for Keller, Michael Minetta.

90
00:04:01,264 --> 00:04:04,565
A man I know very well. You could
coordinate your efforts with him.

91
00:04:04,568 --> 00:04:05,839
- Really?
- Yes.

92
00:04:05,842 --> 00:04:09,077
I'll arrange a meeting.
But move fast, Archie.

93
00:04:09,080 --> 00:04:12,800
Every hour that passes, our killer
could be planning his next attack.

94
00:04:15,663 --> 00:04:17,263
Any word from Chic?

95
00:04:18,151 --> 00:04:21,500
No. He hasn't called since I
took him to the bus station.

96
00:04:21,503 --> 00:04:24,437
So who knows? Maybe he's gone for good.

97
00:04:26,980 --> 00:04:28,894
Hey, the silver lining to all this Chic

98
00:04:28,897 --> 00:04:30,877
stuff over the last
couple of weeks is...

99
00:04:30,880 --> 00:04:33,546
That's as bad as it gets, Betty.

100
00:04:33,548 --> 00:04:35,481
It can't get worse, how could it?

101
00:04:35,484 --> 00:04:37,800
My dad could be the Black Hood.

102
00:04:37,803 --> 00:04:42,159
Yeah, okay. Well, that would be worse.

103
00:04:46,925 --> 00:04:48,525
Well, well, well...

104
00:04:49,667 --> 00:04:52,999
Aren't you boys a handsome
assortment of he-devils?

105
00:04:53,002 --> 00:04:56,065
Veronica, these young men have
come to pay their respects.

106
00:04:56,068 --> 00:04:57,668
Oh, I know why they're here, Mom.

107
00:04:57,671 --> 00:05:00,905
And while I'm dying to hear
proposals, I'm already late for school.

108
00:05:00,908 --> 00:05:02,841
But maybe I can squeeze you in tomorrow?

109
00:05:02,844 --> 00:05:05,845
Uh... Tomorrow?

110
00:05:05,848 --> 00:05:08,394
You do things your way,
Mom, I do things mine.

111
00:05:10,545 --> 00:05:12,918
There's no one else that I can talk to.

112
00:05:12,921 --> 00:05:15,955
No one else who might understand
what I'm going through.

113
00:05:15,958 --> 00:05:19,112
Dear cousin, you look
harrowed. What is it?

114
00:05:19,115 --> 00:05:22,523
Cheryl, before you saw
the video of your dad...

115
00:05:22,526 --> 00:05:24,964
shooting Jason...

116
00:05:24,966 --> 00:05:27,433
Did you know that he was the murderer?

117
00:05:27,436 --> 00:05:30,903
Subconsciously, yes. Why do you ask?

118
00:05:32,774 --> 00:05:35,775
I think there's a chance that my dad...

119
00:05:36,878 --> 00:05:38,511
That somehow...

120
00:05:41,349 --> 00:05:43,449
He might be the Black Hood.

121
00:05:45,193 --> 00:05:49,362
Oh. Oh, Betty, I don't know.

122
00:05:49,365 --> 00:05:52,391
I've seen your pater
sneak around Thistlehouse,

123
00:05:52,393 --> 00:05:54,927
and he has all the stealth
of a marshmallow man.

124
00:05:54,930 --> 00:05:56,730
Wherefore comes this accusation?

125
00:05:56,733 --> 00:05:58,133
It's just intuition.

126
00:05:58,136 --> 00:06:00,499
Cheryl, I don't want
my dad to be a murderer.

127
00:06:00,501 --> 00:06:02,534
It would destroy our lives even more,

128
00:06:02,537 --> 00:06:05,004
but I don't know...

129
00:06:05,007 --> 00:06:07,589
I can feel it in my bones...

130
00:06:09,434 --> 00:06:12,168
If you're coming to me for advice, fine.

131
00:06:12,171 --> 00:06:13,628
Let's get you to the Po-Po.

132
00:06:13,631 --> 00:06:15,305
Maybe this new Sheriff
has half a brain...

133
00:06:15,308 --> 00:06:17,483
No. No. No. yet.

134
00:06:17,486 --> 00:06:20,519
I need to be sure before
I involve anyone else.

135
00:06:20,522 --> 00:06:22,121
Also, I know it's hard to explain,

136
00:06:22,123 --> 00:06:23,689
but if my dad is the Black Hood,

137
00:06:23,692 --> 00:06:27,761
I need to be the one who
confronts him, who stops him.

138
00:06:28,796 --> 00:06:32,440
In that case, absorb
my hard-learned advice.

139
00:06:32,443 --> 00:06:35,200
You need concrete proof,
or a confession, or both.

140
00:06:35,203 --> 00:06:37,425
First step? Buy yourself
time while you investigate.

141
00:06:37,428 --> 00:06:39,261
That means pretending
everything is normal.

142
00:06:39,264 --> 00:06:41,364
Yeah, well, luckily,
that's my specialty.

143
00:06:41,367 --> 00:06:45,444
You're playing a very
dangerous game, Betty Cooper.

144
00:06:48,849 --> 00:06:51,816
I don't think he would
hurt his own daughter.

145
00:06:53,455 --> 00:06:56,808
And I never thought my dad would
shoot his son in the forehead,

146
00:06:56,811 --> 00:06:58,624
but that's the world we live in.

147
00:07:00,350 --> 00:07:01,883
Tread carefully, cousin.

148
00:07:09,504 --> 00:07:11,237
You and Fred are neck-and-neck,

149
00:07:11,239 --> 00:07:13,815
and with the town divided over
our prison, this debate is...

150
00:07:13,818 --> 00:07:16,541
Is the single most important
event of the election.

151
00:07:16,544 --> 00:07:18,628
I know. I know, basta.

152
00:07:18,631 --> 00:07:20,912
We already control the Sheriff's
office, and The Register,

153
00:07:20,915 --> 00:07:24,128
but we need the Mayor's office as
well, so the prison can't be blocked.

154
00:07:24,131 --> 00:07:26,398
I'm hoping Archie's Dark
Circle will cause unrest.

155
00:07:26,401 --> 00:07:28,653
After all, if Fred can't
control his own son,

156
00:07:28,656 --> 00:07:32,658
he certainly can't control a town
on the verge of sliding into chaos.

157
00:07:34,388 --> 00:07:36,922
If what happened to
Midge taught us anything,

158
00:07:36,925 --> 00:07:39,130
it's that no one is safe, anywhere.

159
00:07:39,133 --> 00:07:41,730
This town needs us, it
needs the Dark Circle.

160
00:07:41,733 --> 00:07:43,773
And this time, we'll have
the new Sheriff's support.

161
00:07:44,407 --> 00:07:46,007
- No offense, Kev.
- None taken.

162
00:07:46,010 --> 00:07:47,940
Here to catch the guy
who cost my dad his job.

163
00:07:47,942 --> 00:07:49,976
Guys, I... I gotta tell you something.

164
00:07:49,979 --> 00:07:52,206
The night of the show, Midge and I got

165
00:07:52,209 --> 00:07:54,748
into a fight backstage
cause she admitted,

166
00:07:54,751 --> 00:07:56,615
she was seeing someone
else, behind my back.

167
00:07:56,617 --> 00:07:58,017
- Who?
- Who?

168
00:07:58,020 --> 00:08:00,052
She let it slip that it was a Serpent.

169
00:08:00,054 --> 00:08:01,287
What?

170
00:08:03,157 --> 00:08:06,959
I knew it, I knew it, the second
they set foot in this school!

171
00:08:06,961 --> 00:08:10,628
Moose, why didn't you say
anything to us? Or my dad?

172
00:08:10,631 --> 00:08:14,042
I didn't want to look like the jealous
boyfriend and have people think that I...

173
00:08:14,045 --> 00:08:17,003
- We should talk to the new Sheriff...
- Screw that!

174
00:08:17,006 --> 00:08:19,472
Some Serpent scumbag was doing Midge.

175
00:08:19,474 --> 00:08:21,307
We just gotta figure out which one.

176
00:08:21,310 --> 00:08:24,810
War Baby called my father
and I from Shankshaw.

177
00:08:24,812 --> 00:08:27,747
Her old adversaries, the
Ghoulies, had been released.

178
00:08:27,749 --> 00:08:29,949
Word on the street is that
they want Serpent blood.

179
00:08:29,958 --> 00:08:32,409
They're gunning for a
re-match. They want war.

180
00:08:33,283 --> 00:08:35,512
Which one of you reptiles
was screwing Midge Klump?

181
00:08:35,515 --> 00:08:37,644
What the hell is going on?
This is a private meeting.

182
00:08:37,647 --> 00:08:40,180
I'm guessing it was you, Sweet Pea.

183
00:08:40,858 --> 00:08:42,140
Reggie, that's enough.

184
00:08:42,143 --> 00:08:44,180
You ass, I didn't even know Midge.

185
00:08:44,183 --> 00:08:47,500
But yeah, I get why she wouldn't
want fleas from you mangy Bulldogs!

186
00:08:47,503 --> 00:08:49,435
- Reggie, no!
- Hey, hey, hey, hey!

187
00:08:49,437 --> 00:08:51,303
Stop fighting now!

188
